metadata.description:
"Explore an alternate history of World War One, as machines of destruction take to the skies...
At the end of 1916, Germany has occupied a large swathe of Northern France and Paris is bombed by fleets of Zeppelins. Among the German commanders is a certain Adolf Hitler; his airship protected by a squadron of planes, led by Hermann Goering. But Hitler and Goering do not know that their destiny is being decided in the decaying Russian Empire, where Rasputin is about to change the history of Europe."
metadata.name: Wunderwaffen presents: Zeppelin's War
